window.__QUIZ_DATA__=[{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>1","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : COMPONENTS OF COMPUTERS","question":"A system is described as a","images":[],"options":{"A":"collection of static hardware components.","B":"digital means of solving problems.","C":"method of computerization.","D":"set of objects connected to form a whole unit."},"answer":"D","explanation":"A system is generally defined as a group of interconnected or interacting elements that work together to form a unified whole. This definition applies broadly, whether in engineering, biology, computing, or other fields.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>2","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION AGE : DATA AND INFORMATION","question":"One method of obtaining data is through","images":[],"options":{"A":"calculation.","B":"conversion.","C":"observation.","D":"transmission."},"answer":"C","explanation":"Observation is a fundamental method of gathering data by directly monitoring or measuring phenomena, events, or behaviors. This can be done manually (e.g., a scientist recording temperatures) or through instruments (e.g., sensors collecting environmental data).","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>3","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION PROCESSING : THE ART OF INFORMATION PROCESSING","question":"The number  B8F  is written in","images":[],"options":{"A":"binary system.","B":"decimal system.","C":"hexadecimal system.","D":"octal system."},"answer":"C","explanation":"The number B8F contains the digit 'B' (which represents the decimal value 11) and the letter 'F' (which represents 15). These alphanumeric characters (A-F) are only used in the hexadecimal (base-16) system.    Hexadecimal numbers are commonly used in computing (e.g., memory addresses, color codes).","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>4","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : CLASSIFICATION OF COMPUTERS","question":"One difference between a desktop computer and a laptop computer is that laptop computer","images":[],"options":{"A":"can be connected directly to the Internet through WiFi but desktop computer can only be connected through Ethernet.","B":"contains high capacity battery that powers it for an extensive period while desktop computer mainly uses UPS for alternative power source.","C":"does not support the use of mouse while desktop computer supports the use of mouse.","D":"uses only serial ports for all connections while desktop computer uses only parallel ports for all connections."},"answer":"B","explanation":"Laptops have built-in rechargeable batteries, allowing them to operate without being plugged in for hours.    Desktops rely on continuous mains power and usually need an Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) for backup during outages.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>5","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : HISTORY OF COMPUTERS","question":"A mechanical device that allows the operation of multiplication through repeated addition is the","images":[],"options":{"A":"Jacquard's Loom.","B":"Pascaline.","C":"Slide Rule.","D":"Stepped Reckoner."},"answer":"D","explanation":"The Stepped Reckoner (invented by Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz in the late 17th century) was a mechanical calculator capable of performing multiplication through repeated addition (and division via repeated subtraction). It used a stepped drum mechanism, making it one of the first machines to automate these operations.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>6","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : HISTORY OF COMPUTERS","question":"Which of the following statements about the Slide Rule are true?    I. Multiplication that goes off the slide can be corrected by resetting the slide.  II. Operations of addition can be carried out by directly adding two or more numbers together on the slide.  III. Logarithm is used to transform the operations of multiplication and division to addition and substraction.","images":[],"options":{"A":"I and II only","B":"I and III only","C":"II and III only","D":"I, II and III"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Statement I is true \u2013 If multiplication exceeds the scale, the slide can be reset to continue the operation.    Statement II is false \u2013 The Slide Rule does not perform direct addition or subtraction of numbers; it is primarily used for multiplication, division, roots, and logarithms.    Statement III is true \u2013 The Slide Rule uses logarithmic scales to convert multiplication and division into addition and subtraction operations.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>7","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : CLASSIFICATION OF COMPUTERS","question":"The following features distinguish the supercomputer from other types of computer except","images":[],"options":{"A":"high processing speed.","B":"number of users connected at once.","C":"physical size.","D":"small memory capacity."},"answer":"D","explanation":"A supercomputer is characterized by its exceptionally high processing speed and large physical size. It handles massive computations and large datasets, thus requiring enormous memory capacity, not small. While capable of handling many tasks, its primary distinction isn't the number of direct human users compared to other types of computers like mainframes. Therefore, having a \"small memory capacity\" is the statement that does not distinguish a supercomputer, as it's the opposite of reality.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>8","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : COMPONENTS OF COMPUTERS","question":"Which of the following statements are true about pointing devices?    I. Device has buttons used to select objects.  II. Device moves an onscreen pointer to allow user select objects.  III. Older types of the device used laser, an optical technology that tracks movements with light while newer types of the device use ball only.  IV. User slides device along a flat surface to move pointer around the screen.","images":[],"options":{"A":"I, II and III only","B":"I, II and IV only","C":"I, III and IV only","D":"I, II, III and IV"},"answer":"B","explanation":"True Statements:  I. \"Device has buttons used to select objects.\"    Most pointing devices (e.g., mice, trackballs) include buttons (left/right click) for selection.    II. \"Device moves an onscreen pointer to allow user to select objects.\"    The primary function of a pointing device is to control a cursor/pointer on the screen.    IV. \"User slides device along a flat surface to move pointer around the screen.\"    This describes traditional mechanical mice (ball-based) and modern optical/laser mice (though they don't require a ball).    False Statement:  III. \"Older types of the device used laser, an optical technology that tracks movements with light while newer types of the device use ball only.\"    Incorrect: Older mice used balls (mechanical), while newer ones use optical/laser sensors. The statement reverses the timeline.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>9","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"LOGIC GATES","question":"Which of the following logic devices is a  non-equivalent  gate?","images":[],"options":{"A":"AND gate","B":"EX-NOR gate","C":"EX-OR gate","D":"NOR gate"},"answer":"C","explanation":"What is a Non-Equivalent Gate?  A non-equivalent gate outputs true (1) when its inputs are different and false (0) when they are the same. This matches the behavior of the EX-OR (XOR) gate.    Truth Table for EX-OR (XOR) Gate:    A\tB\tOutput0\t0\t00\t1\t11\t0\t11\t1\t0  Outputs 1 only when inputs differ (non-equivalent).","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>10","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"LOGIC GATES","question":"Use the logic devices in Figures 1 and 2 to answer questions 10 to 12 given that the input variables X and Y have values of 0011 and 0101 respectively.      Compute the value of the output Z in Figure 1 using the values of X and Y given.","images":["data:image/jpeg;base64,"],"options":{"A":"1110","B":"1000","C":"0001","D":"0111"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Figure 1 represents an AND gate.    An AND gate's output (Z) is HIGH (1) only if both of its inputs (X and Y) are HIGH (1). Otherwise, the output is LOW (0).    Given input values:    X = 0011  Y = 0101  Let's compute Z for each corresponding bit:    X\tY\tZ = X AND Y0\t0\t00\t1\t01\t0\t01\t1\t1  So, the value of the output Z is 0001.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>11","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"LOGIC GATES","question":"Use the logic devices in Figures 1 and 2 to answer questions 10 to 12 given that the input variables X and Y have values of 0011 and 0101 respectively.    If the input variable X in Figure 1 is passed through the device in Figure 2 before going into the logic gate in Figure 1, what will be the output Z?","images":["data:image/jpeg;base64,"],"options":{"A":"1001","B":"0100","C":"1101","D":"1110"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Figure 1 is an AND gate.  Figure 2 is a NOT gate.    The problem states that input variable X is first passed through the NOT gate (Figure 2) before going into the AND gate (Figure 1). This means the inputs to the AND gate will be the NOT of X (let's call this X') and the original Y. The output will be Z = X' AND Y.    Given input values:    X = 0011  Y = 0101    Step 1: Compute X' (NOT X)  A NOT gate inverts its input.  If X = 0011, then X' = NOT(0011) = 1100.    Step 2: Compute Z = X' AND Y  Now we perform an AND operation with X' and Y.    X' (NOT X)\tY\tZ = X' AND Y1\t0\t01\t1\t10\t0\t00\t1\t0  So, the value of the output Z is 0100.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>12","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"LOGIC GATES","question":"Use the logic devices in Figures 1 and 2 to answer questions 10 to 12 given that the input variables X and Y have values of 0011 and 0101 respectively.    If the input variable Y in Figure 1 is passed through the device in Figure 2 before going into the logic gate in Figure 1, compute the output at Z.","images":["data:image/jpeg;base64,"],"options":{"A":"1101","B":"0100","C":"0010","D":"0001"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Figure 1 is an AND gate.  Figure 2 is a NOT gate.    This time, the input variable Y is passed through the NOT gate (Figure 2) before entering the AND gate (Figure 1). The inputs to the AND gate will be the original X and the NOT of Y (let's call this Y'). The output will be Z = X AND Y'.    Given input values:    X = 0011  Y = 0101  Step 1: Compute Y' (NOT Y)  A NOT gate inverts its input.  If Y = 0101, then Y' = NOT(0101) = 1010.    Step 2: Compute Z = X AND Y'  Now we perform an AND operation with X and Y'.    X\tY' (NOT Y)\tZ = X AND Y'0\t1\t00\t0\t01\t1\t11\t0\t0  So, the value of the output Z is 0010.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>13","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : COMPONENTS OF COMPUTERS","question":"Which of the following memory capacities is the largest?","images":[],"options":{"A":"1 TB","B":"100 GB","C":"500 MB","D":"960 KB"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Here's the comparison of the options in bytes (smallest to largest):    960 KB = 960 \u00d7 1,024 = 983,040 bytes    500 MB = 500 \u00d7 1,024\u00b2 = 524,288,000 bytes    100 GB = 100 \u00d7 1,024\u00b3 = 107,374,182,400 bytes    1 TB = 1 \u00d7 1,024\u2074 = 1,099,511,627,776 bytes    Key Conversion:    1 TB = 1,024 GB (largest unit here).    100 GB is 10% of 1 TB, making it smaller.    500 MB and 960 KB are significantly smaller.    Therefore, 1 TB (terabyte) is the largest capacity.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>14","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"LOGIC GATES","question":"Which one of the following statements is true about logic gates?","images":[],"options":{"A":"The output of AND gate is low if both inputs are high.","B":"The output of AND gate is high if both or either of the inputs is low.","C":"The output of NOT gate is high if the input is low.","D":"The output of OR gate is low if both inputs are high."},"answer":"C","explanation":"A NOT gate (also called an inverter) has only one input. It inverts the input signal. If the input is LOW (0), the output is HIGH (1), and if the input is HIGH (1), the output is LOW (0).","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>15","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"A set of instructions written in the language of the computer to solve user's problem is called","images":[],"options":{"A":"assembler.","B":"byte.","C":"pseudocode.","D":"software."},"answer":"D","explanation":"Software: This is a general term for sets of instructions, data, or programs used to operate computers and execute specific tasks. The instructions are written in a language that the computer can understand (ultimately translated into machine code).    Let's look at the other options:    Assembler: This is a type of program that translates assembly language (a low-level programming language) into machine code. It's a tool used in the software development process, not the set of instructions itself.    Byte: This is a unit of digital information that typically consists of eight bits. It's a unit of data storage, not a set of instructions.    Pseudocode: This is an informal high-level description of the operating principle of a computer program or other algorithm. It's written in a human-readable format, often using structural conventions of a normal programming language but without strict syntax. It's a way to plan software, not the final instructions the computer executes.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>16","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : OPERATING SYSTEM","question":"In computer operation, loading and starting of application programs is carried out by","images":[],"options":{"A":"device drivers.","B":"embedded system.","C":"operating system.","D":"peripheral devices."},"answer":"C","explanation":"The operating system (OS) is responsible for loading and starting application programs. It manages system resources, handles memory allocation, and ensures programs run smoothly.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>17","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : OPERATING SYSTEM","question":"The operating system is responsible for","images":[],"options":{"A":"checking the effect of virus on the computer.","B":"creating tasks for computer programmers.","C":"making the most efficient use of the computer hardware.","D":"teaching new skills to computer users through videos."},"answer":"C","explanation":"The operating system (OS) is the core software that manages hardware resources (CPU, memory, storage, etc.) to ensure:    Efficiency: Allocates CPU time, memory, and I/O devices optimally.    Fairness: Prevents one program from monopolizing resources.    Abstraction: Simplifies hardware interaction for applications (e.g., file systems, device drivers).","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>18","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : OPERATING SYSTEM","question":"Which one of the following statements explains the function of utility software?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Converts source code to object code","B":"Enables hardware to communicate with the computer","C":"Helps to clean disk space and manages installation of applications","D":"Helps to improve the functionality of hardware devices"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Utility software is designed to help manage, maintain, and optimize a computer system. Common functions include:    - Disk cleanup    - File management    - Installing/uninstalling applications    - System monitoring    - Backup and recovery","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>19","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"The clear and precise step-by-step procedure of solving a particular problem is called","images":[],"options":{"A":"algorithm.","B":"flowchart.","C":"interpretation.","D":"programming."},"answer":"A","explanation":"An algorithm is a well-defined, step-by-step procedure for solving a problem or accomplishing a task. It provides a clear and unambiguous sequence of instructions that, when executed, will lead to the desired outcome.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>20","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"A program written in source code can be converted to object code by","images":[],"options":{"A":"code converter.","B":"language translator.","C":"operating system.","D":"utility software."},"answer":"B","explanation":"A language translator converts source code (human-readable code, e.g., Python, C++) into object code (machine-readable binary). There are three main types:    1. Compiler: Translates the entire source code at once (e.g., GCC for C).    2. Interpreter: Translates and executes line-by-line (e.g., Python interpreter).    3. Assembler: Converts assembly language to machine code.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>21","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"The process of searching for errors and eliminating them in a computer program is called","images":[],"options":{"A":"compilation.","B":"debugging.","C":"execution.","D":"normalization."},"answer":"B","explanation":"Debugging is the systematic process of:    1. Identifying errors (bugs) in a program.    2. Analyzing their causes (e.g., logic mistakes, syntax issues).    3. Fixing the errors to ensure the program runs correctly.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>22","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"Use the QBASIC program below to answer question 22.  10 REM Multiplication Table Construction  20 CLS  30 FOR 1% = 1 TO 50  40 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;C = 1  50 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;FOR J% = 1 TO 50  60 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PRINT TAB(C) J% * 1%  70 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;C = C + 3  80 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;NEXT J%  90 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PRINT  100 NEXT 1%  110 END    The main function of the statement in line 20 in the QBASIC program above is to","images":[],"options":{"A":"assign variable names before the execution of the current program.","B":"create memory location for all the variables that will be declared in the current program.","C":"erase previously printed output on the screen before the output of the current program.","D":"indicate that the current program is command based."},"answer":"C","explanation":"In QBASIC, the CLS (CLear Screen) command clears the screen, erasing any previously printed output before displaying new output.    So the main function of line 20 is to:    erase previously printed output on the screen before the output of the current program.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>23","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"Which one of the following statements is correct about the rules of flowcharting?","images":[],"options":{"A":"All symbols of flowchart are connected with Terminal Box to show the logical connection between them","B":"All flowchart process symbols are connected with On page connector to show the flow of operation","C":"All flowcharts start with a Start Box and end with a Decision Box","D":"The flow of Control must always enter an object from top to bottom"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The flow of Control must always enter an object from top to bottom. This is a convention in flowcharting that promotes clarity and readability. While flow lines can exit a symbol in different directions (e.g., from the bottom or sides for branching in decision boxes), the standard practice is to have the primary flow of control enter a process or other symbol from the top.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>24","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"The major difference between low level programming languages and high level programming languages is that","images":[],"options":{"A":"high level languages are less memory efficient while low level languages are more memory efficient.","B":"high level languages will not need a translator but low level languages will do.","C":"low level languages are slower while high level languages are faster.","D":"low level languages are interpreted while high level languages are assembled."},"answer":"A","explanation":"Low-level languages (like assembly language) provide direct control over hardware and memory, allowing skilled programmers to optimize memory usage. High-level languages abstract away many of these details, often leading to less memory-efficient code by default, although modern compilers do perform optimizations.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>25","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"In computer programming, source codes are usually translated to intermediate codes in order to","images":[],"options":{"A":"avoid the need for full native compiler for every new machine that will run the program.","B":"change the analysis portion for different compilers.","C":"prevent modification of the program source code by unauthorized persons.","D":"prevent the synthesis part of the compiler from changing for any target machine."},"answer":"A","explanation":"Intermediate Code (e.g., Bytecode): By compiling the source code into an intermediate representation, you create a platform-independent code. This intermediate code can then be executed by a virtual machine (VM) or further translated into native machine code specific to each target architecture. This approach has several advantages:    - Portability: The same intermediate code can run on any machine that has a compatible VM or a relatively simple just-in-time (JIT) compiler for that intermediate code. This significantly reduces the effort required to make a program run on different operating systems and hardware.    - Faster Porting: Instead of writing a full compiler from scratch for each new platform, developers only need to create or adapt the VM or JIT compiler for the intermediate code.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>26","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : NETWORKING","question":"The set of rules by which communication takes place over a network is called","images":[],"options":{"A":"connectivity.","B":"ethics.","C":"protocol.","D":"topology."},"answer":"C","explanation":"In networking, a protocol is a set of rules and procedures that govern how data is transmitted and received over a network. These rules define the format, timing, sequencing, and error handling of data exchange between devices.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>27","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : NETWORKING","question":"Which one of the following pairs contains types of network topology?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Token and Mesh","B":"Star and Token","C":"Ring and Bus","D":"Bus and Node"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Network Topology refers to the physical or logical arrangement of nodes (devices) and connections in a network. Common types of network topologies include:     - Ring Topology: Devices are connected in a closed loop or ring.  - Bus Topology: All devices are connected to a single central cable (the bus).  - Star Topology: All devices connect to a central hub or switch.  - Mesh Topology: Devices are interconnected with many redundant connections.  - Tree Topology: A combination of star and bus topologies.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>28","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : APPLICATION OF ICT IN EVERYDAY LIFE","question":"An advantage of using Computer Aided Manufacturing in car manufacturing industry is that","images":[],"options":{"A":"cost of equipment is low.","B":"equipment does not require close supervision.","C":"pollution is reduced.","D":"products follow consistent standards."},"answer":"D","explanation":"Computer Aided Manufacturing (CAM) systems use precise computer control to direct manufacturing processes. This ensures that each component and the final product are manufactured to exact specifications, leading to higher levels of consistency and quality across the entire production line.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>29","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : NETWORKING","question":"The Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol ( TCP/IP ) is used to","images":[],"options":{"A":"interconnect devices on the Internet.","B":"retrieve email from a mail server.","C":"transfer files from a server to a client.","D":"send email from one user to another."},"answer":"A","explanation":"TCP/IP (Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol) is the fundamental communication protocol suite that enables devices to connect and exchange data across the Internet and other networks. Its primary functions include:    - Device Interconnection: Assigns unique IP addresses to devices (e.g., computers, servers) and routes data packets between them.    - Reliable Data Delivery:    1. TCP ensures error-checked, ordered delivery (e.g., loading a webpage).    2. IP handles addressing and routing (e.g., sending packets to the correct destination).","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>30","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : NETWORKING","question":"One difference between intranetworking and internetworking is that","images":[],"options":{"A":"intranetworking is more secured compared to internetworking.","B":"intranetworking has unlimited coverage compared to internetworking.","C":"intranetworking is publicly owned while internetworking is privately owned.","D":"intranetworking can be accessed by everyone while internetworking is accessible to the staff of an organization only."},"answer":"A","explanation":"Intranetworking refers to the communication within a single private network, such as an organization's local area network (LAN). It is generally more secure because it is restricted to authorized users within the organization.    Internetworking involves the connection of multiple networks, such as the connection of LANs via the internet. This broader connectivity exposes systems to more external threats, making it less secure than a closed intranet.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>31","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : PROCESS OF INFORMATION TRANSMISSION","question":"Which one of the following statements is true about email client?","images":[],"options":{"A":"It is a server which stores email messages","B":"It is a program which enables users to send and receive email","C":"It is a person using email services to serve the public","D":"It is a computer which provides email services to users"},"answer":"B","explanation":"An email client is a software application that users install on their computers, phones, or access through a web browser. This program allows them to compose, send, receive, organize, and manage their email messages. Examples include Microsoft Outlook, Mozilla Thunderbird, Apple Mail, and web-based clients like Gmail and Yahoo Mail accessed in a browser.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>32","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"A record in a database can be identified using","images":[],"options":{"A":"a key field.","B":"an attribute key.","C":"an entity relationship.","D":"an object identifier."},"answer":"A","explanation":"A key field is an attribute or a set of attributes within a database table that uniquely identifies each record (row) in that table. This ensures that you can distinguish and access specific pieces of information. Examples include a customer ID, a product serial number, or a combination of fields that together are unique.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>33","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : SPREADSHEET","question":"Which one of the following software can be used by a company accountant to prepare staff payment?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Microsoft Word","B":"Microsoft Publisher","C":"Microsoft PowerPoint","D":"Microsoft Excel"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Microsoft Excel is a spreadsheet application widely used by accountants for tasks such as:    - Calculating staff salaries    - Creating payroll sheets    - Managing financial records    - Automating calculations with formulas and functions","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>34","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"In MS Access, the first object to be created which will enable user to create or use other objects is a","images":[],"options":{"A":"Form.","B":"Macro.","C":"Report.","D":"Table."},"answer":"D","explanation":"In Microsoft Access, a table is the foundational object where data is stored. All other objects\u2014forms, queries, reports, and macros\u2014are based on the data contained in tables.    You cannot create meaningful forms, reports, or macros without having at least one table with data to work on.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>35","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : SPREADSHEET","question":"The Microsoft Excel menu bar icon in Figure 3 represents a command used to","images":["data:image/jpeg;base64,"],"options":{"A":"change the row height or column width, organize sheets, protect or hide cells.","B":"continue a series or pattern into neighbouring cells in any direction.","C":"remove the selection and put it on the clipboard so that user can paste it somewhere else.","D":"wrap extra-long text into multiple lines to allow a user view all of it."},"answer":"D","explanation":"The Microsoft Excel menu bar icon in Figure 3 represents a command used to wrap extra-long text into multiple lines to allow a user view all of it.    The icon shows text wrapping within a cell.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>36","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : GRAPHIC PACKAGES","question":"The CorelDraw Toolbox object in Figure 4 is used to","images":["data:image/jpeg;base64,"],"options":{"A":"select and transform objects.","B":"edit the shape of objects.","C":"draw lines and curves.","D":"change the magnification level in drawing window."},"answer":"B","explanation":"The CorelDraw Toolbox object in Figure 4 is indeed the Shape Tool, which is used to edit the shape of objects.    The Shape Tool allows users to manipulate the nodes and control handles of vector objects to precisely alter their form.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>37","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : PRESENTATION PACKAGE","question":"Which one of the following statements is true about the Slide Sorter View in Microsoft PowerPoint?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Only the texts of all slides are shown","B":"Preview presentation takes place","C":"Slide time appears on the screen","D":"Thumbnail versions of all slides are arranged"},"answer":"D","explanation":"In Slide Sorter View in Microsoft PowerPoint, you see small thumbnail images of all the slides in the presentation arranged on one screen. This view helps you easily rearrange, add, or delete slides.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>38","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"Arrange the following steps in the correct order of creating queries in Microsoft Access.  I. Choose the tables to include in the query.  II. Choose the fields to include and adjust the criteria.  III. Click the CREATE > Query Design button on the ribbon.  IV. Click the RUN button/switch to Data Sheet View.","images":[],"options":{"A":"I, II, III, IV","B":"I, II, IV, III","C":"II, I, III, IV","D":"III, I, II, IV"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Step-by-Step Explanation for Creating a Query in Microsoft Access:    III. Click the CREATE > Query Design button on the ribbon.    This is the first step to initiate the query design process. It opens the Query Design view.    I. Choose the tables to include in the query.    Once in the Query Design view, the \"Show Table\" dialog box appears (or you can manually add tables). You select the tables that contain the data you want to retrieve or work with in your query.    II. Choose the fields to include and adjust the criteria.    After adding the tables, you select the specific fields from those tables that you want to display in your query results. You also define any criteria (conditions) to filter the data and retrieve only the records that meet your requirements.    IV. Click the RUN button/switch to Data Sheet View.    Finally, after designing your query by selecting tables, fields, and setting criteria, you run the query to see the results in Data Sheet View. The \"RUN\" button executes the query based on your design.    Therefore, the logical sequence is to first open the query designer, then select the data sources (tables), specify what data you want (fields) and any conditions (criteria), and finally execute the query to see the output.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>39","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : INTERNET","question":"A small picture or object that represents a file, program, webpage or comment in windows is called","images":[],"options":{"A":"a taskbar.","B":"a toolbar.","C":"an icon.","D":"an image."},"answer":"C","explanation":"An icon is a small graphical representation that symbolizes:    - Files (e.g., a PDF icon).    - Programs (e.g., Chrome's colorful ball).    - Webpages (e.g., favicons in browser tabs).    - Functions (e.g., trash bin for deletion).    Icons provide a visual way for users to quickly identify and interact with these items.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>40","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS : PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL)","question":"The two main types of user interface are","images":[],"options":{"A":"visual user interface and command driven interface.","B":"soft user interface and graphical user interface.","C":"graphical user interface and visual user interface.","D":"graphical user interface and command driven interface."},"answer":"D","explanation":"The two main types of user interface are graphical user interface and command driven interface.    Here's why:    - Graphical User Interface (GUI): This type of interface allows users to interact with a computer through visual elements such as icons, menus, windows, and buttons. Users typically use a mouse, trackpad, or touch screen to navigate and interact with these elements. Examples include Windows, macOS, Android, and iOS.    - Command-Driven Interface (CLI): This type of interface requires users to interact with the computer by typing specific text commands. The computer responds by displaying text output. Examples include the command prompt in Windows (cmd.exe), the terminal in macOS and Linux (bash, zsh), and older operating systems like MS-DOS.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>41","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : OPERATING SYSTEM","question":"To initiate the startup process, the BIOS requires","images":[],"options":{"A":"date, hardware status and system configuration.","B":"date, time and system configuration.","C":"date, time, data file and hardware status.","D":"date, time, hardware status and text file."},"answer":"B","explanation":"BIOS (Basic Input/Output System) is a firmware embedded on a computer's motherboard. One of its primary functions during startup (the POST - Power-On Self Test) is to initialize the system hardware and prepare it for the operating system to load. To do this effectively, the BIOS needs certain fundamental pieces of information:  - Date and Time: The system's real-time clock is checked and initialized.  - System Configuration: This includes details about the installed hardware components (CPU, memory, hard drives, etc.), their settings, and the boot order (which device to try to load the operating system from).","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>42","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : MAINTENANCE OF COMPUTER","question":"A desktop computer is switched on and the monitor displays an error message which reads: No input signal. The likely cause of this error is","images":[],"options":{"A":"defective monitor.","B":"disconnected VGA cable.","C":"low memory.","D":"power failure."},"answer":"B","explanation":"The error message \"No input signal\" on a monitor usually means the monitor is not receiving any video signal from the computer. The most common cause is a disconnected or loose VGA (or HDMI/DisplayPort) cable between the monitor and the computer.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>43","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION PROCESSING : THE ART OF INFORMATION PROCESSING","question":"The parts of the EBCDIC are","images":[],"options":{"A":"nibbles and bytes.","B":"strings and integers.","C":"words and numbers.","D":"zone bits and numerical bits."},"answer":"D","explanation":"EBCDIC (Extended Binary Coded Decimal Interchange Code)\u00a0is an 8-bit character encoding system primarily used in IBM mainframes. Its structure divides each 8-bit byte into two parts:    1. Zone Bits (First 4 bits): Define the\u00a0category\u00a0of the character (e.g., letters, symbols).    Example:\u00a01100\u00a0for uppercase letters.    2. Numerical Bits (Last 4 bits): Specify the\u00a0value\u00a0within the category.    Example:\u00a00001\u00a0for 'A' (1100 0001\u00a0in full EBCDIC).","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>44","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION PROCESSING : THE ART OF INFORMATION PROCESSING","question":"The binary number 100101 can be written in denary as","images":[],"options":{"A":"25.","B":"37.","C":"45.","D":"211."},"answer":"B","explanation":"1001012 =  (1 \u00d7 25) + (0 \u00d7 24) + (0 \u00d7 23) + (1 \u00d7 22) + (0 \u00d7 21) + (1 \u00d7 20)    = (1 \u00d7 32) + 0 + 0 + (1 \u00d7 4) + 0 + (1 \u00d7 1)    = 32 + 0 + 0 + 4 + 0 + 1    = 37","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>45","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION PROCESSING : THE ART OF INFORMATION PROCESSING","question":"Convert 70 from base ten to octal.","images":[],"options":{"A":"0188","B":"1068","C":"6018","D":"8108"},"answer":"B","explanation":"87088 rem 681 rem 00 rem 1  \u2234 7010 = 1068 (moving from bottom to top)","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>46","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : SAFETY MEASURES","question":"Backing up of computer files is the process of","images":[],"options":{"A":"updating files in the computer main storage area.","B":"storing extra copy of files in the main memory of the computer.","C":"storing extra copy of files in an external storage location.","D":"storing extra copy of files on the computer main storage area."},"answer":"C","explanation":"Backing up is the process of creating a duplicate of your computer files and storing it in a separate location. This is done as a safeguard against data loss due to hardware failure, software corruption, accidental deletion, or other unforeseen events. The key is that the backup is stored outside of your computer's primary storage.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>47","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : FILE ORGANIZATION","question":"The file structure is represented systematically in ascending order as","images":[],"options":{"A":"data \u2192 field \u2192 record \u2192 file.","B":"record \u2192 data \u2192 file \u2192 field.","C":"field \u2192 record \u2192 data \u2192 file.","D":"file \u2192 record \u2192 field \u2192 data."},"answer":"A","explanation":"The file structure is represented systematically in ascending order of complexity and size as:    data \u2192 field \u2192 record \u2192 file.    Here's why:    - Data: The most basic unit, representing raw facts or values.  - Field: A collection of related characters (data) that represents a single attribute of an entity (e.g., a name, an age, a product code).  - Record: A collection of related fields that describe a single instance of an entity (e.g., all the information about one specific customer).  - File: A collection of related records (e.g., a file containing the records of all customers).    Therefore, the hierarchy builds from individual pieces of data up to a complete file containing multiple related entities.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>48","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : SAFETY MEASURES","question":"Which of the following statements supports the goals of data backup?  I. Need for duplication.  II. Need for future reference.  III. Protection against data loss.","images":[],"options":{"A":"I and II only","B":"I and III only","C":"II and III only","D":"I, II and III"},"answer":"D","explanation":"All three statements fully support the core goals of data backup:    I. \"Need for duplication\" \u2192    Backups create redundant copies of data to ensure availability if the original is lost/corrupted.    II. \"Need for future reference\" \u2192    Backups preserve data for long-term access (e.g., archival records, compliance).    III. \"Protection against data loss\" \u2192    The primary purpose of backups is to safeguard against risks like hardware failure, cyberattacks, or accidental deletion.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>49","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : COMPUTER ETHICS","question":"The unauthorized use of computer and network resources is known as","images":[],"options":{"A":"hacking.","B":"phishing.","C":"piracy.","D":"spamming."},"answer":"A","explanation":"Hacking refers to the unauthorized access, use, or manipulation of computer systems, networks, or data, often with malicious intent. It encompasses activities like:    - Exploiting vulnerabilities to gain access.    - Disrupting services (e.g., DDoS attacks).    - Stealing sensitive information.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Computer Studies>2025>50","subject":"Computer Studies","year":"2025","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : NETWORKING","question":"Poor implementation of network or lack of ICT policies may result to","images":[],"options":{"A":"phishing.","B":"security breach.","C":"spamming.","D":"virus infection."},"answer":"B","explanation":"Weak network implementation (e.g., open ports, default passwords, unpatched systems) and the absence of clear ICT policies (e.g., password requirements, access controls, data handling procedures) create vulnerabilities that malicious actors can exploit to gain unauthorized access to systems and data. This is the essence of a security breach.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"}];